block_list.title: Video Tutorial
block_list.body: This is Paper plane 24 of our 100 Exotic Paper Airplane Challenge. The Shuttlecock designed by Michael G. LaFosse. This one flies really straight. This is an origami plane folded from a square sheet. Enjoy!!! If you missed my last Exotic Paper Airplane "Paper Plane 023 : Chuck Finn by Michael G. LaFosse", you could watch it at https://youtu.be/_5ioFyaVjY4 Here at Heap Art, we are trying to help you practice origami on a regular bases. Every week I will select a minimum of 2 origami models and show you how to fold it. If you like origami and paper airplanes -- Please use the following link to subscribe to my channel: https://www.youtube.com/c/heapart?sub_confirmation=1 My Upload Schedule: Tuesday : A new Paper Airplane, part of my 100 Exotic Paper Airplane Challenge Friday : A new Origami Model never seen before on my channel Thanks for watching. Wilson Lee
